oc:kn_3ad35319 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All briefing modes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Briefs should be actionable: every item should have a clear next step or reason for inclusion. Keep briefs concise — link to source materials rather than reproducing them in full." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Legal professionals need to quickly triage and act, not read lengthy reproductions of source documents" .

oc:kn_6dd7174d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After generating any briefing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always note which sources were unavailable or returned errors prominently so the user knows what was not checked. Always note the limitations of the sources searched." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incomplete source coverage creates false confidence; the user must know blind spots to make informed decisions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7819b1c6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Incident brief mode only" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never wait for complete information when generating incident briefs — speed matters. Produce the brief quickly with available information and flag gaps." ;
    oc:hasRationale "In developing legal situations, delayed context can lead to missed notification deadlines (e.g., GDPR 72-hour window) and preservation failures" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ab91ac1c a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Incident brief mode" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For incident briefs: flag litigation hold/preservation obligations immediately, note privilege considerations (mark as attorney-client privileged/work product if appropriate), and flag applicable notification deadlines (e.g., 72 hours GDPR for data breaches)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are time-sensitive legal obligations with severe consequences for non-compliance" .

oc:kn_dd12f357 a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Topic brief mode" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Topic briefs synthesize connected sources only — they do not substitute for formal legal research. If the topic requires current legal authority or case law, recommend consulting a legal research platform (Westlaw, Lexis) or outside counsel." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Internal sources lack current case law and statutory authority; relying solely on them for legal conclusions is dangerous" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f95a2c5a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All briefing modes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Scans multiple enterprise systems (email, calendar, chat, CLM, CRM) and reads potentially sensitive legal communications and documents." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Agent must handle privileged communications appropriately and maintain confidentiality" .

oc:kn_fbd1e825 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All briefing modes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill assists with legal workflows but does NOT provide legal advice. All briefings must be reviewed by qualified legal professionals before being relied upon." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI-generated briefings cannot replace professional legal judgment and could expose the user to risk if treated as authoritative legal guidance" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

